      align: [left, top]
      text: |
        <p><strong>Literature Taxonomy</strong></p>
        <p style="margin-top:4px">Long-document attention mechanisms can be categorized into three paradigms: (1) <strong>Sparse Attention</strong> (Child et al., 2019; Zaheer et al., 2020) restricts pairwise interactions to predefined patterns; (2) <strong>Linear Attention</strong> (Katharopoulos et al., 2020; Choromanski et al., 2021) approximates softmax with kernel methods achieving \(O(n)\) complexity; (3) <strong>Hierarchical Methods</strong> (Pappagari et al., 2019; Zhang et al., 2022) process documents at multiple resolutions but lack end-to-end differentiability.</p>

